{"id":50913,"title":"Management of diabetic ketoacidosis in adults.","abstract":"Ketoacidosis is a serious complication of diabetes. It is commonly precipitated by poor adherence to medication, stress and concurrent illness; it can be life threatening if it is not addressed quickly and effectively. This article discusses the pathophysiology, diagnosis and management of the condition, and highlights the nurse's role in this.","date":"2014-04-18","categories":"Endocrine System Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24741880","annotations":[{"name":"Diabetes mellitus","weight":0.797552,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diabetes_mellitus"},{"name":"Pharmaceutical drug","weight":0.70749,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pharmaceutical_drug"},{"name":"Stress (biology)","weight":0.635135,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stress_(biology)"},{"name":"Diabetic ketoacidosis","weight":0.488317,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diabetic_ketoacidosis"},{"name":"Diagnosis","weight":0.468165,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diagnosis"},{"name":"Illness","weight":0.446138,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Illness"},{"name":"Complication (medicine)","weight":0.382633,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Complication_(medicine)"},{"name":"Nurse","weight":0.101782,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nurse"},{"name":"Ketoacidosis","weight":0.0491452,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ketoacidosis"},{"name":"Pathophysiology","weight":0.0287296,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pathophysiology"},{"name":"Management","weight":0.0227187,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Management"},{"name":"Precipitation (chemistry)","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Precipitation_(chemistry)"},{"name":"Concurrency (road)","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wik